Measures if your scores for the category are above or below the final score on average. Calculated by subtracting the final score from your score for the category then taking the average of those values. A value of 0 implies your scores are centered around the final score, a negative value means your scores tend to be lower than the final score, while a postive value implies your scores tend to be above the final value. Values less than +/-0.1 are good while values more extreme than +/-0.3 indicate work is needed.